1
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:41,360
He!

2
00:01:51,040 --> 00:01:52,160
He!

3
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:53,800
He!

4
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:01,160
<i>He!</i>

5
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:06,200
<i>He!</i>

6
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:10,639
In 2002, my dad
had a stroke for the first time,

7
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:13,320
and he fell into the rooftop shaft.

8
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:14,960
And then,

9
00:02:15,920 --> 00:02:18,720
he was heavily injured in an operation.

10
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,520
And later,

11
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:27,160
the sudden passing of his apprentice
exacerbated his condition.

12
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,880
Two years ago, he went into retirement.

13
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:30,760
Out of nowhere, he received
something left behind by his apprentice.

14
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:33,000
Perhaps it triggered something in him.

15
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:35,840
His condition acted up, and he fainted.

16
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:38,440
In his mind, his apprentice never died.

17
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:41,200
He merely went to Beijing
to teach for 12 years.

18
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:43,720
Whenever his apprentice appeared,

19
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:46,640
he'd convince him to stay
to help him investigate cases.

20
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:51,000
It seems like his memory is stuck in 2002.

21
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,760
I waited for you for five years!

22
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:22,000
Why didn't you save me?

23
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:23,360
Why?

24
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:25,560
Come back.

25
00:03:26,160 --> 00:03:28,120
I'm waiting for you. Come down.

26
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:30,600
Keep me company. You…

27
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:03,160
Doctor.

28
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:04,680
Doctor!

29
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:08,120
He. You're awake.

30
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:10,160
Why am I here?

31
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,839
You fell into the rooftop shaft yesterday.

32
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:19,519
Fortunately, no bone fractures.
Just some cuts.

33
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:20,800
Fortunately?

34
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:22,079
Officer He,

35
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:25,080
you fell because you had a stroke,
and you lost consciousness.

36
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:26,240
I checked your medical records.

37
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:28,040
Your cholesterol, blood sugar,
and blood pressure levels

38
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:29,240
are dangerously high.

39
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:30,680
Did you take medication regularly?

40
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:33,800
Taking pills during all three of my meals?

41
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:35,120
Who can live like that?

42
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:36,120
Listen.

43
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:38,360
Your condition is serious.
You have to take your medication.

44
00:04:38,440 --> 00:04:40,600
Otherwise, this will happen again,

45
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:42,680
- and it will be more serious.
- Okay.

46
00:04:43,640 --> 00:04:45,040
There are no other huge issues,

47
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,880
but you will stay here for a few days.

48
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:48,160
Thanks, Doctor.

49
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:03,400
Captain Feng just left.

50
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:06,000
He told me everything.

51
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:10,720
Are you intending
to take full responsibility?

52
00:05:11,840 --> 00:05:14,840
Did you tell Captain Feng
that you want to go to Beijing to teach?

53
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:26,440
He.

54
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:32,600
I'd like to apologize to you.
It's my fault.

55
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:36,080
Whether it's the missing persons case
or the homicide,

56
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:39,600
I shouldn't have brought
my emotions into the case.

57
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:49,760
Give me your hand.

58
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,000
- That hand.
- Why?

59
00:05:53,960 --> 00:05:54,800
Press this.

60
00:05:57,520 --> 00:05:59,080
He, what are you doing?
What about your IV drip?

61
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:01,040
Now is not the time to lie down.

62
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,920
Let's go. We have a case to crack.

63
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:07,160
Come.

64
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:14,720
In the June 30th case,

65
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:17,520
Song Qingsong is undeniably
the main suspect.

66
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:21,200
But he allegedly fled
to the US five years ago.

67
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:23,840
Immigrating is suspicious enough.

68
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:26,200
Back then, Song Qingsong
hired someone to commit a murder.

69
00:06:26,280 --> 00:06:29,120
But he was acquitted
due to a lack of evidence.

70
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:31,120
We could only charge him with bribery.

71
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:32,960
Even then, it wasn't that serious.

72
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:34,920
He would get five years in jail at most.

73
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:37,080
And when he would be released,
he would still be the same old him.

74
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:40,080
The factory, the car,
and the property would still be his.

75
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:41,680
So why did he flee?

76
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:43,480
I did investigate him.

77
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:45,520
Song Qingsong had dealings in both
legitimate and illegitimate channels.

78
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:47,680
He's definitely not a good person,

79
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:49,600
but he's kind to his factory workers.

80
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:51,360
Those workers have worked
for him for more than a decade.

81
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:55,000
Oh. He also has a son
who was only three years old when he fled.

82
00:06:56,160 --> 00:07:00,360
So there's probably another story
behind his hiring of the hitman.

83
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:02,480
The most effective way

84
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:04,720
to investigate Song Qingsong
is through Wu Shanlong.

85
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:07,640
But after he took over the cement factory,
he accrued debts

86
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:09,120
and is now in hiding.

87
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:11,880
Turn right at the intersection in front.

88
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,160
We're not returning to the station?

89
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:16,000
Shouldn't we find Wu Shanlong?

90
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:25,920
HONGYUN HUIHUANG CLUB

91
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:40,520
Who are you?

92
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:42,320
This is the dressing room.

93
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:47,920
Are you new here?

94
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:52,600
I'm Wu. W-U.

95
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:54,640
Shanlong is my name.

96
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:58,760
I am the biggest shareholder of this club.

97
00:07:58,840 --> 00:08:00,920
Qingsong Cement Factory. Ever heard of it?

98
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,280
It's mine too.

99
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:07,120
Perhaps I could book all of you today,

100
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:10,840
so that you can get some good rest.

101
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,040
Hi, Mei.

102
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:15,080
- Hi, Mei.
- Hi, Mei.

103
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:16,720
Hi.

104
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,520
Come out here.

105
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:40,720
Leeching off this place every day.

106
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:44,000
Do I owe you anything or what?

107
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:51,000
Did I hear that correctly?

108
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:53,280
Do you even know who you're talking to?

109
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:55,040
Wu Shanlong.

110
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:57,360
From now on,

111
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:59,520
I won't lend a single cent to you.

112
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:05,280
Zhao Hongmei. I see you've grown arrogant.

113
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:06,760
Without me,

114
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:08,920
you would still have been the owner
of that small massage parlor.

115
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,600
Who gave you your first fortune?

116
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:12,240
It was me, Wu Shanlong. It was me.

117
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:14,280
Without me, this place would still
be called Dahuihuang.

118
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:20,000
You helped me?

119
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,680
Do you even have the wits for it?

120
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:23,120
Without me,

121
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:25,080
Song Qingsong would still
be running the cement factory,

122
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:28,120
- and you would still be his chauffeur.
- What did you say?

123
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:30,160
- I gave you your share of the money.
- Say that again.

124
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:32,480
I gave you your share of the money.
You are just incompetent.

125
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:35,120
The cement factory was a gold mine,
but you messed it up.

126
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:38,480
And now, you're leeching off me.

127
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:41,240
I've treated you with enough generosity.

128
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:43,320
Am I the shareholder here or not?

129
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:45,240
I can come and go whenever I want.

130
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:47,960
Of course. Come whenever you want.

131
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:50,920
But before you come,

132
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:53,680
clean up the mess you made.

133
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:55,200
What mess?

134
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:57,000
Tell me. What mess?

135
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,640
Still playing dumb?

136
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:01,040
The police just released a statement.

137
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:03,960
Xu Zhihong's body was found in Yuanlongli.

138
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:05,600
They are investigating it everywhere now.

139
00:10:09,560 --> 00:10:10,800
You killed Xu Meng too.

140
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:14,120
You are now a murderer.

141
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:15,920
Why don't you learn
from your brother-in-law?

142
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:18,840
Just run away. Run.

143
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:21,560
When you're gone, everyone will be safe.

144
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:24,000
The girls under me?

145
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:27,640
I can't guarantee
they are as loyal as I am.

146
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:29,600
If one of them gets drunk
and runs their mouth,

147
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:31,000
I won't be able to stop them.

148
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:32,800
Sure.

149
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:35,960
I can run away.

150
00:10:36,040 --> 00:10:38,120
But I need you to give me some money.

151
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:39,760
Are you crazy?

152
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:52,000
Zhao Hongmei.

153
00:10:53,920 --> 00:10:56,120
You're talking to a murderer now.

154
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:59,800
How many lives do you risk by defying me?

155
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:06,680
Defying you? What about that?

156
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:08,920
What about that?
I won't comply, so kill me now.

157
00:11:10,640 --> 00:11:12,920
Do you want to see
if I will go to the police right now?

158
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,440
Please be patient, sir.

159
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:16,120
Our manager is having a meeting. You…

160
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:23,240
What a coincidence.
My two old friends are here.

161
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:25,160
Great. Let's hang out.

162
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:29,480
Officer He. Officer Ran. You're here.

163
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:32,760
I was just reminiscing
about the past with Mr. Wu here.

164
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:33,920
We talked about you two.

165
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:36,880
- Speak of the devil, really.
- Is that so?

166
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:39,040
- Zhang!
- Yes?

167
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:40,920
How is the speaker outside going?

168
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:43,320
- It's almost done, Mei.
- Show me.

169
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:46,360
I have work to do. Mr. Hu,

170
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:48,920
entertain our old friends here, will you?

171
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,040
I'll count on you. Take a seat.

172
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:51,800
Order anything you want. Take a seat.

173
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:53,800
Take a seat.

174
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:54,840
Officer Ran!

175
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:56,840
You're more handsome than before.

176
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:12,000
Speak.

177
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:14,360
Tell us about Xu Meng and her father.

178
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:17,720
What are you on about, Officer He?

179
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:19,480
I don't know them.

180
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:24,640
Wu Shanlong,

181
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:27,280
between us, there's no need to play coy.

182
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:34,360
Back then, Song Qingsong hired a hitman
to kill Xu Meng and her father.

183
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:36,240
You did it, didn't you?

184
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,480
How did Xu Zhihong die?

185
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:45,280
Where is Xu Meng? Is she dead or alive?

186
00:12:50,280 --> 00:12:51,400
Speak!

187
00:12:56,920 --> 00:12:58,960
I'll speak. Officer He,
I'll tell you everything.

188
00:12:59,040 --> 00:13:00,120
I'll come clean.

189
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:02,400
I'll tell you everything.

190
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:04,960
Song Qingsong gave me 40,000 yuan

191
00:13:05,040 --> 00:13:06,640
to get rid of Xu Meng and her father.

192
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:08,640
He doesn't care about laws, but I do.

193
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:11,440
I paid you to get rid of them,

194
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:12,560
and what did you do?

195
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:13,920
I asked you to do it yourself,

196
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,400
but you paid someone else
to do it instead.

197
00:13:15,480 --> 00:13:17,800
That deal could have cost me my life.

198
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:20,720
I wouldn't have done it,
even if he had punched me to death.

199
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:21,920
What about Wolfie?

200
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:25,560
You know him very well, don't you?

201
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:28,680
Get rid of them.

202
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:36,000
What? What wolf?

203
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:38,000
I don't know him.

204
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:39,600
Sure.

205
00:13:39,680 --> 00:13:41,640
You said it had nothing to do with you.

206
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:43,000
Then tell me.

207
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,840
How did Xu Zhihong die?

208
00:13:48,680 --> 00:13:51,280
Based on my understanding
of Song Qingsong,

209
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:53,280
he must have hired someone else to do it.

210
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:55,600
Achieve his goals at all costs.

211
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:56,880
That's his personality.

212
00:13:56,960 --> 00:14:00,120
Why must Song Qingsong
get rid of Xu Meng and her father?

213
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,440
I know why.

214
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:02,920
Back then, Xu Meng

215
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,840
saw the tender document
inside Song Qingsong's briefcase

216
00:14:04,920 --> 00:14:05,840
in the foot massage parlor.

217
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:08,600
Then, she wrote to Song Qingsong
to extort money.

218
00:14:08,680 --> 00:14:10,280
Song Qingsong was furious

219
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:11,920
and wanted her gone.

220
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,040
Getting rid of her father
was just an afterthought.

221
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:15,920
Why didn't you tell us back then?

222
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:19,080
Because he was my brother-in-law.

223
00:14:19,160 --> 00:14:20,560
But now, it's different.

224
00:14:20,640 --> 00:14:22,680
Just ask me whatever you want to know.

225
00:14:22,760 --> 00:14:24,440
I'll tell you everything I know.

226
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:37,480
Wu Shanlong.

227
00:14:37,560 --> 00:14:41,320
Have you contacted
Song Qingsong in recent years?

228
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:45,840
We lost contact five years ago.

229
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:48,760
I don't know where he's hiding now.

230
00:14:51,920 --> 00:14:52,960
Sir,

231
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:55,280
if he contacts me,

232
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:59,840
I promise to contact
the police right away.

233
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:46,360
Wu Shanlong. Do not leave Weiyang.

234
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:47,880
We will talk to you anytime.

235
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:51,760
Sure, sir. I won't leave.

236
00:15:53,080 --> 00:15:54,720
Drop by when you're free.

237
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:09,920
HONGYUN HUIHUANG CLUB

238
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:24,160
That liar.

239
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:26,160
Not a word of truth from his mouth.

240
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:28,120
I made sure to ask him about Wolfie,

241
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:29,800
and his eyes looked to the right.

242
00:16:31,520 --> 00:16:33,400
He knows that we don't have evidence,

243
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:34,960
and we can't do anything about him.

244
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:40,440
Now that the lead
on Song Qingsong is stuck,

245
00:16:40,520 --> 00:16:43,240
we can only find
another breakthrough in the scene.

246
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:48,200
He.

247
00:16:48,280 --> 00:16:50,720
I want to go through
the suspicious residents

248
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:51,640
in Yuanlongli again.

249
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:54,400
You still want to head to Yuanlongli?

250
00:16:55,280 --> 00:16:56,800
What if you're stuck in there?

251
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:03,160
He.

252
00:17:03,680 --> 00:17:05,280
Have you heard
of the Eye of the Vortex Theory?

253
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:06,839
What?

254
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:09,920
The eye of the vortex
is the center of the vortex.

255
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,200
To see it,

256
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:13,240
you must venture into the vortex.

257
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:15,599
New York Block
is at the center of the crime,

258
00:17:15,680 --> 00:17:16,800
the eye of the vortex.

259
00:17:16,880 --> 00:17:18,880
Residents might come and go,

260
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:21,440
but as long as the building's there,
we will find useful leads.

261
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:30,040
What?

262
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:31,960
You almost had it there.

263
00:17:32,040 --> 00:17:33,840
I thought you had lost your mind.

264
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:43,320
LIANG JUAN

265
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:44,760
Yes, Officer Liang?

266
00:17:48,440 --> 00:17:49,440
Okay. Got it.

267
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:50,920
What's wrong?

268
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:53,000
The Forensic Department
said they found toxins

269
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:54,360
in Xu Zhihong's skull.

270
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:56,080
- What kind of toxin?
- They are analyzing it.

271
00:17:57,440 --> 00:18:00,040
Let's do it this way.
We'll split up and search.

272
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:01,400
You'll head to Yuanlongli.

273
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:03,560
I'll head to the station
to ask Liang for more information.

274
00:18:03,640 --> 00:18:04,520
Okay.

275
00:18:07,120 --> 00:18:08,160
Oh.

276
00:18:08,240 --> 00:18:10,120
If you're taking the same route,

277
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:11,960
can you pick Xiaohe up for me at school?

278
00:18:12,560 --> 00:18:13,960
I've been busy lately.

279
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:16,760
I haven't seen her in a week.

280
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:23,320
Are you and your wife…

281
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:28,240
Don't be nosy. Just do your work.

282
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:47,600
I'LL PICK XIAOHE UP TODAY

283
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:48,800
SEND MESSAGE

284
00:18:52,520 --> 00:18:53,400
DATE, TIME, VIEW OPTIONS

285
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:54,800
RECIPIENT: YUN

286
