I BOUGHT FISH TODAY

287
00:18:56,240 --> 00:18:58,520
WILL YOU BE HOME FOR DINNER TODAY?

288
00:18:58,600 --> 00:18:59,440
DATE, TIME, VIEW OPTIONS

289
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:00,680
RECIPIENT: YUN

290
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:03,200
TOMORROW IS THE PARENT-TEACHER DAY

291
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:04,880
WHO'S GOING? YOU OR ME?

292
00:19:41,120 --> 00:19:43,920
WEIYANG NO. 1 MIDDLE SCHOOL

293
00:20:00,360 --> 00:20:01,800
I like your palm.

294
00:20:02,960 --> 00:20:05,000
Show me your right palm.

295
00:20:06,720 --> 00:20:07,800
Xiaohe.

296
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:09,600
Uncle Ran.

297
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:11,800
My uncle came to pick me up.
I have to go now. Bye!

298
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,880
- Uncle Ran.
- Long time no see.

299
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:17,840
Are you here for a case?

300
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:20,440
Your dad asked me to pick you up.

301
00:20:22,120 --> 00:20:23,200
Oh.

302
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:24,680
He finally remembers he has a daughter.

303
00:20:27,080 --> 00:20:28,920
Come on. He has a business trip this week.

304
00:20:33,160 --> 00:20:35,760
You have changed your style.

305
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:38,800
People change.

306
00:20:38,880 --> 00:20:41,680
I was too childish.
It's not too late to grow up now.

307
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:05,320
Put your legs down. It's dangerous.

308
00:21:11,360 --> 00:21:13,160
<i>Tomorrow, June 8th,</i>

309
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:14,840
<i>our national team in Group C</i>

310
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:16,680
<i>will face the strongest opponent</i>
<i>in the group,</i>

311
00:21:16,760 --> 00:21:17,840
<i>the Brazil team,</i>

312
00:21:17,920 --> 00:21:19,880
<i>who is highly anticipated</i>
<i>to win the World Cup.</i>

313
00:21:19,960 --> 00:21:24,680
<i>Let's hope that at 7:30 p.m. tomorrow,</i>
<i>our national team can create a miracle.</i>

314
00:21:24,760 --> 00:21:26,000
<i>There's only one way to find out.</i>

315
00:21:26,080 --> 00:21:27,000
<i>Passion</i>

316
00:21:27,080 --> 00:21:30,880
<i>Fighting for the glory of the team</i>

317
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:32,480
<i>Come on, come on</i>

318
00:21:33,680 --> 00:21:34,880
<i>Power</i>

319
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:38,960
<i>We will never bow under the sky</i>

320
00:21:39,560 --> 00:21:40,880
<i>Raise your hand</i>

321
00:21:40,960 --> 00:21:42,560
<i>Passion</i>

322
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:47,040
<i>Fighting for the glory of the team</i>

323
00:21:47,560 --> 00:21:48,880
<i>Raise your hand</i>

324
00:21:48,960 --> 00:21:50,320
<i>Power</i>

325
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:02,280
This is not the way back to my home.

326
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:04,520
Are you trying to kidnap me?

327
00:22:05,920 --> 00:22:07,040
Don't worry.

328
00:22:07,120 --> 00:22:08,720
No one wants to kidnap

329
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:11,240
a wild brat like you unless
there's something wrong with their brain.

330
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:21,360
Why did you stop singing?

331
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:23,960
Oh, no. It's Friday today.

332
00:22:24,040 --> 00:22:26,240
Uncle Ran, can you drive me
to the band's rehearsal?

333
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:28,080
They are waiting for me.

334
00:22:28,160 --> 00:22:31,920
No. I promised He to take you home.

335
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:33,280
After that, I have a case to investigate.

336
00:22:36,120 --> 00:22:37,760
Are you going to Yuanlongli?

337
00:22:40,440 --> 00:22:41,480
It's on the way.

338
00:22:56,480 --> 00:22:59,240
Liang. What did you find in his skull?

339
00:23:00,080 --> 00:23:03,240
We found excessive arsenic
in Xu Zhihong's skull.

340
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:06,200
He was fed poison
for a long time before he died.

341
00:23:06,280 --> 00:23:08,240
It might be trisenox.

342
00:23:09,480 --> 00:23:10,880
Trisenox?

343
00:23:10,960 --> 00:23:12,080
Arsenic, basically.

344
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:13,840
CONCLUSION: EXCESSIVE ARSENIC
FOUND IN THE VICTIM'S SKULL

345
00:23:29,360 --> 00:23:31,480
Xiaohe. Slow down. Wait for me.

346
00:23:31,560 --> 00:23:33,560
UNDERGROUND CAR PARK

347
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:38,840
Uncle Ran.

348
00:23:38,920 --> 00:23:42,440
Are you investigating the skull?

349
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:44,600
How did you know?

350
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:46,880
Everyone in the underground scene knows.

351
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:49,120
I knew you were involved in this case.

352
00:23:50,280 --> 00:23:52,320
You guys rehearse down here?

353
00:23:53,040 --> 00:23:55,160
Yes. What's so shocking about that?

354
00:23:55,240 --> 00:23:57,800
Many Western bands began in the garage.

355
00:23:59,120 --> 00:24:01,480
What role do you play in your band?

356
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:04,360
Lead vocal and bassist.

357
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:06,360
Oh.

358
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:08,280
I also write songs. I just wrote one.

359
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:10,920
Uncle Ran, quick.

360
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:14,600
The acoustics in this spot are good.
Our keyboardist found it.

361
00:24:15,520 --> 00:24:16,920
Guys, I'm here.

362
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:18,360
DO NOT THROW ANYTHING INSIDE
DO NOT TRESPASS

363
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:38,200
Uncle Ran. Just investigate your case.

364
00:24:38,280 --> 00:24:39,200
I'll head back once the rehearsal is over.

365
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:42,200
I'll pick you up after two hours.

366
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:46,320
Hi, Officer Ran.

367
00:24:46,920 --> 00:24:47,760
You're…

368
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:49,680
The keyboardist I told you about.

369
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:52,920
You don't recognize me? I live upstairs.

370
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:55,360
You chased after me back then.

371
00:24:57,440 --> 00:24:59,560
Little boy, your wounds are…

372
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:01,320
I fell when he chased after me.

373
00:25:03,480 --> 00:25:04,640
Oh, it's you.

374
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:07,320
He might look fragile,

375
00:25:07,400 --> 00:25:09,720
but he can man up if need be.

376
00:25:09,800 --> 00:25:12,640
He risked his life

377
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:15,000
and took these instruments
out of his dad's bar.

378
00:25:15,080 --> 00:25:16,720
They call me the instrument sponsor.

379
00:25:18,160 --> 00:25:19,040
GENERAL WARD

380
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:19,960
Ms. Wang.

381
00:25:20,960 --> 00:25:22,200
Officer He.

382
00:25:22,280 --> 00:25:23,560
Did Han Zi'ang say anything?

383
00:25:30,520 --> 00:25:32,080
He woke up just now.

384
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:35,560
But no matter what the doctor or I said,

385
00:25:36,480 --> 00:25:38,320
he wouldn't react to us.

386
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:41,800
The doctor said he had…

387
00:25:41,880 --> 00:25:43,120
Post-traumatic stress disorder?

388
00:25:43,720 --> 00:25:44,880
Yes.

389
00:25:45,560 --> 00:25:47,880
Madam Wang. Calm down now.

390
00:25:47,960 --> 00:25:50,200
Han Zi'ang encountered a traumatic event.

391
00:25:50,280 --> 00:25:52,160
His mind and his body
need time to recover.

392
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:55,160
We're running out of time, Officer He.

393
00:25:55,240 --> 00:25:57,120
The school called me.

394
00:25:57,200 --> 00:25:59,840
They will release
his expulsion notice tomorrow.

395
00:26:00,440 --> 00:26:02,120
- Officer He. I'm begging you.
- Please.

396
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:04,520
Get up now. I'll call the principal now.

397
00:26:15,520 --> 00:26:18,080
<i>Yesterday, several parents</i>
<i>escalated the issue to the board meeting.</i>

398
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:20,080
<i>The school is under immense pressure.</i>

399
00:26:20,160 --> 00:26:22,760
<i>Besides, the police didn't make</i>
<i>any meaningful progress.</i>

400
00:26:22,840 --> 00:26:25,160
Principal Qin, I understand
the difficulty of your position.

401
00:26:25,240 --> 00:26:26,160
Han Zi'ang just woke up now.

402
00:26:26,840 --> 00:26:28,360
I will uncover the truth
as soon as possible.

403
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:30,680
Then, the criminal department
will release a statement.

404
00:26:31,280 --> 00:26:32,960
<i>Officer He, can you give me a deadline?</i>

405
00:26:33,040 --> 00:26:33,920
<i>Not too long.</i>

406
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:36,440
<i>I need to justify myself</i>
<i>before the board and the parents.</i>

407
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:38,800
Seven days. Just seven days.

408
00:27:00,880 --> 00:27:02,440
Mister. Hello.

409
00:27:02,520 --> 00:27:03,960
Have you seen the child in this photo?

410
00:27:04,040 --> 00:27:05,240
No.

411
00:27:07,120 --> 00:27:08,040
Hi, mister.

412
00:27:08,120 --> 00:27:09,760
Have you seen the child in this photo?

413
00:27:09,840 --> 00:27:10,760
Not at all.

414
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:12,000
Hi.

415
00:27:12,080 --> 00:27:13,640
Have you seen this child?

416
00:27:13,720 --> 00:27:14,560
No.

417
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:16,600
Hi. Have you seen this child?

418
00:27:16,680 --> 00:27:17,520
No.

419
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:23,760
Mr. He.

420
00:27:28,320 --> 00:27:29,440
Qiao.

421
00:27:29,520 --> 00:27:30,440
What are you doing here?

422
00:27:31,120 --> 00:27:32,400
I'm here to see a doctor.

423
00:27:32,480 --> 00:27:34,640
How do you feel now?

424
00:27:37,800 --> 00:27:40,000
You introduced the doctor to Xiaohe?

425
00:27:40,080 --> 00:27:42,080
She could've told me earlier.

426
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:46,040
Wait.

427
00:27:46,120 --> 00:27:48,840
You're still so young.
What are you doing here?

428
00:27:48,920 --> 00:27:51,160
I'm working for the Redevelopment Bureau,

429
00:27:51,240 --> 00:27:53,440
and I have to talk to residents
who refuse to move.

430
00:27:53,520 --> 00:27:55,040
It's stressful.

431
00:27:55,120 --> 00:27:56,480
I have no one to talk to,

432
00:27:56,560 --> 00:27:58,920
so I come here to talk to my therapist.

433
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:03,200
Have you not found a partner
after all these years?

434
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:05,920
I'm not in a rush.

435
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:09,400
Having a partner is nice,

436
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:12,240
but I can't find anyone as sweet

437
00:28:14,280 --> 00:28:16,240
as Ran anymore.

438
00:28:19,560 --> 00:28:20,400
Qiao.

439
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:24,360
We can't just live in the past.

440
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:27,040
We have to move on.

441
00:28:37,840 --> 00:28:40,160
Officer Ran. Sorry for the long wait.

442
00:28:41,120 --> 00:28:42,160
I have the name list

443
00:28:42,240 --> 00:28:43,800
of all residents who lived
in New York Block in 1997.

444
00:28:43,880 --> 00:28:45,480
- Take a look.
- Thank you so much, Ma Qiang.

445
00:28:45,560 --> 00:28:48,240
Don't mention it.
Let me know if you need help.

446
00:28:52,160 --> 00:28:53,800
1997 YUANLONGLI HOUSEOWNERS
TENANTS REGISTRATION FORM

447
00:29:13,280 --> 00:29:14,320
Officer Ran.

448
00:29:39,600 --> 00:29:40,960
After I entered through the gate,

449
00:29:41,040 --> 00:29:43,560
I saw a familiar silhouette
and thought it was you.

450
00:29:43,640 --> 00:29:44,640
Turns out I am right.

451
00:29:46,960 --> 00:29:47,920
It's been so long.

452
00:29:48,840 --> 00:29:50,520
How have you been?

453
00:29:51,040 --> 00:29:52,240
Yes.

454
00:29:52,320 --> 00:29:55,560
All of us have been busy in recent years.

455
00:29:55,640 --> 00:29:57,920
I enrolled in the adult classes
of Weiyang University,

456
00:29:58,000 --> 00:29:59,320
and I graduated last year.

457
00:30:00,720 --> 00:30:02,880
What are you working as right now?

458
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:06,080
I am now interning
in an insurance company.

459
00:30:10,320 --> 00:30:12,280
You encouraged me

460
00:30:12,360 --> 00:30:14,960
to be more confident
and to make more friends.

461
00:30:16,080 --> 00:30:18,080
And I did make more friends

462
00:30:18,160 --> 00:30:20,480
and met my neighbors.

463
00:30:20,560 --> 00:30:23,920
The rumors about me have stopped.

464
00:30:27,240 --> 00:30:28,360
That's great.

465
00:30:30,480 --> 00:30:31,320
Thank you.

466
00:30:34,760 --> 00:30:36,240
You… You're injured.

467
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:38,160
You didn't even treat your injuries.

468
00:30:39,280 --> 00:30:40,560
Just some cuts. It's nothing.

469
00:30:40,640 --> 00:30:41,680
That's no good.

470
00:30:52,120 --> 00:30:53,520
CASUAL SNEAKERS

471
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:56,200
You're being reckless.

472
00:30:56,280 --> 00:30:58,080
Wounds are no joking matter.

473
00:31:08,360 --> 00:31:09,200
Come.

474
00:31:52,960 --> 00:31:53,880
Do you remember?

475
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:55,800
When we first met,

476
00:31:55,880 --> 00:31:58,080
it was you who treated my wounds.

477
00:31:58,680 --> 00:31:59,520
Yes.

478
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:02,520
I was quite clumsy back then.

479
00:32:02,600 --> 00:32:04,840
Unlike you.

480
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:08,280
Actually,

481
00:32:08,360 --> 00:32:11,280
my first job was a carer.

482
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:13,440
I worked in this apartment.

483
00:32:13,520 --> 00:32:15,400
Ma Qiang told me before.

484
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:18,760
You cared for an old man.

485
00:32:20,920 --> 00:32:21,760
Yes.

486
00:32:24,960 --> 00:32:26,120
Oh.

487
00:32:26,880 --> 00:32:30,800
Why did you come to Weiyang
from Guangxi? For work?

488
00:32:32,880 --> 00:32:36,760
When I was little, my parents split up.

489
00:32:37,480 --> 00:32:39,440
My dad moved abroad with my sister,

490
00:32:39,520 --> 00:32:42,720
and I lived with my mom in Guangxi.

491
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:45,880
But after a few years,

492
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:51,280
my mom passed away due to an illness.

493
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:56,840
I had learned some nursing skills
in my night school,

494
00:32:57,440 --> 00:33:00,080
so I asked my relatives to get me a job.

495
00:33:00,160 --> 00:33:01,920
That was how I came to Yuanlongli.

496
00:33:02,520 --> 00:33:05,560
When the old man
passed away due to an accident,

497
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:07,840
I had nowhere else to go.

498
00:33:07,920 --> 00:33:09,800
So, I continued to rent this place.

499
00:33:13,640 --> 00:33:16,480
It must have been tough on you
surviving on your own.

500
00:33:17,640 --> 00:33:20,080
But no need to carry everything
on your shoulders.

501
00:33:20,160 --> 00:33:21,520
If you need help,

502
00:33:22,960 --> 00:33:24,440
just come to me.

503
00:33:26,680 --> 00:33:27,960
Don't worry.

504
00:33:28,040 --> 00:33:30,240
The toughest part has already passed.

505
00:33:31,440 --> 00:33:33,280
I'm seeing the silver lining now.

506
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:39,080
But…

507
00:33:42,440 --> 00:33:43,360
Yes?

508
00:33:43,440 --> 00:33:46,000
DAJIANCHANG NEIGHBORHOOD

509
00:35:44,200 --> 00:35:46,160
After the incident on the rooftop,

510
00:35:46,240 --> 00:35:49,760
I always feel that someone
is staring at me at midnight.

511
00:35:50,360 --> 00:35:51,720
It's creepy.

512
00:36:08,720 --> 00:36:10,680
Qiao. If you run into trouble,

513
00:36:10,760 --> 00:36:11,960
just call me.

514
00:36:15,120 --> 00:36:16,800
Thank you, Officer Ran.

515
00:36:16,880 --> 00:36:18,120
You're welcome.

516
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:21,880
Give me a moment.

517
00:36:23,480 --> 00:36:24,520
Qing.

518
00:36:29,480 --> 00:36:31,920
Qing. A thief broke in again.

519
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:32,960
What about your place?

520
00:36:33,040 --> 00:36:35,480
- Exactly. Did you lose anything?
- That guy again?

521
00:36:35,560 --> 00:36:36,840
Yes.

522
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:39,400
What's wrong?

523
00:36:42,720 --> 00:36:44,560
Oh, your hidden boyfriend.

524
00:36:44,640 --> 00:36:46,080
Why didn't you tell us?

525
00:36:46,160 --> 00:36:47,800
No. Don't say that.

526
00:36:47,880 --> 00:36:51,120
This is Ran Fangxu. Officer Ran.
He's here to investigate.

527
00:36:52,320 --> 00:36:55,320
Mr. Officer, there's a pervert
in this building.

528
00:36:55,960 --> 00:36:56,880
We live in Unit 1713.

529
00:36:56,960 --> 00:36:58,640
Our clothes that we hung to dry

530
00:36:58,720 --> 00:37:00,480
and our shoes were all stolen by a thief.

531
00:37:00,560 --> 00:37:03,120
I reported it to the management,
but Qian Dajun doesn't care at all.

532
00:37:03,200 --> 00:37:05,600
Also, that pervert also stole lingerie.

533
00:37:05,680 --> 00:37:07,240
- Disgusting!
- That's right.

534
00:37:07,320 --> 00:37:09,280
Mr. Officer, you must intervene.

535
00:37:10,520 --> 00:37:12,520
Don't worry.
I'll investigate this properly.

536
00:37:12,600 --> 00:37:14,320
No need to investigate.

537
00:37:14,400 --> 00:37:16,920
We all know who the pervert is.

538
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:18,240
- Yes. We know.
- That's right.

539
00:37:41,720 --> 00:37:42,640
Speak.

540
00:37:43,240 --> 00:37:44,720
Why do you stare at the unit
belonging to the Xus?

541
00:37:45,360 --> 00:37:47,520
I… No, I didn't do that.

542
00:37:47,600 --> 00:37:48,760
I didn't do that.

543
00:37:48,840 --> 00:37:49,880
You didn't?

544
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:52,000
Let's speak at the police station then.

545
00:37:52,080 --> 00:37:52,920
Come.

546
00:37:54,520 --> 00:37:56,120
I'll come clean.

547
00:37:56,200 --> 00:37:58,040
I did do it.

548
00:38:03,480 --> 00:38:07,120
Someone paid me to do it.

549
00:38:07,200 --> 00:38:09,680
In the summer of 1996,

550
00:38:09,760 --> 00:38:13,800
someone paid me 500 yuan
to spy on the unit opposite.

551
00:38:13,880 --> 00:38:16,360
He told me to call him

552
00:38:16,440 --> 00:38:18,560
if I found anything unusual.

553
00:38:18,640 --> 00:38:21,160
You've been spying on them
for six years just for 500 yuan?

554
00:38:22,360 --> 00:38:25,120
A work accident left me handicapped.

555
00:38:25,200 --> 00:38:26,560
And I'm divorced.

556
00:38:26,640 --> 00:38:29,720
I live all alone in this apartment.

557
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:32,080
I need something to entertain myself.

558
00:38:32,160 --> 00:38:33,320
Speak.

559
00:38:34,520 --> 00:38:35,680
Who hired you?

560
00:38:35,760 --> 00:38:37,760
What's his name? What does he look like?

561
00:38:38,520 --> 00:38:39,400
It was a man.

562
00:38:39,480 --> 00:38:41,920
I don't know his name.

563
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:44,440
He looked like he was around 25 years old.

564
00:38:44,520 --> 00:38:46,960
He was tall and bespectacled.

565
00:38:47,040 --> 00:38:49,760
He had a 30/70 side part,
and he looked like a gentleman.

566
00:39:31,960 --> 00:39:33,680
What a jerk.

567
00:39:33,760 --> 00:39:36,080
I won't forgive you.
